The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Feb. 11: GMR-Fraport today said all information, including a case relating to an airport project in Manila, was declared in its bid application. Reportedly, the Philippines Supreme Court had ruled a $650-million contract with Philippines International Air Terminal Company, where Fraport is a consortium partner, as illegal and fraught with irregularities. Fraport has also sought arbitration by the World Bank in the ongoing Manila case.

 New Delhi, Feb. 11: NTPC is in a fix over the appointment of Ashok Mishra as an independent director on its board, as he is also on Reliance Industries? board. NTPC has moved the court for effecting a gas supply agreement against RIL. The PSU has asked Mishra to give a declaration to assess whether his presence on both the boards could lead to a clash of interests.

 New Delhi, Feb. 11: The government may revisit certain grey areas in service tax in the forthcoming budget, sources said.




